  Check Model History properties (15-Jan-2019 11:51:41)

Check models for edited Model History property values
Check that parameters in the Model Properties dialog History pane use the default tags. In the MDL file format you can configure some model properties to make use of source control tool keyword substitution. If you save your model in SLX format, source control tools cannot perform keyword substitution. Any information in the model file from such keyword substitution is cached when you first save the MDL file as SLX, and is never updated again. The Model Properties History pane and any Model Info blocks in your model show stale information from then on.

  Identify lookup table blocks that generate expensive out-of-range checking code (15-Jan-2019 11:51:41)

These settings can lead to inefficient code generation when inputs always fall within the range of valid breakpoint values for lookup table blocks, including Lookup Table blocks, Prelookup blocks and Interpolation blocks.

Warning
The following lookup table blocks generate out-of-range checking code. If the inputs always fall within the range of valid breakpoint values, you can remove the range-checking code for embedded code generation on a block-by-block basis.

Blocks Parameters Recommended settings
..../Subsystem/1-D Lookup Table Remove protection against out-of-range input in generated code on
..../Subsystem/1-D Lookup Table1 Remove protection against out-of-range input in generated code on


Recommended Action
To automatically fix the warning for all listed blocks, click the "Modify" button and then rerun the check. To manually fix the warning, click the block hyperlink to identify the block. Double-click the block to open the block parameters dialog box. In the block parameters dialog box, manually apply the recommended settings. In addition, we also recommend you to set the 'DiagnosticForOutOfRangeInput' in the block parameters dialog box to 'Warning' or 'Error' to detect any out-of- range inputs during simulation.
